<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-6613 SERIES - REASSEMBLE -
        SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>SYNCHRONIZER ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the sliding clutch, recessed side up, on the pins of the low speed synchronizer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030f9">Figure 159</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030f9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030f9" filename="../figg13/G13030f9.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 159. Install Sliding Clutch on Pins of Low Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the three springs in the direct synchronizer (
                <hotlnk></hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030g0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030g0" filename="../figg13/G13030g0.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 160. Install Springs in Direct Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the direct synchronizer over the low speed blocker pins, seating the springs against
                the pins (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030g1">Figure 161</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030g1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030g1" filename="../figg13/G13030g1.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 161. Place Direct Synchronizer Over Low Speed Blocker Pins</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Compress the springs to fully seat the direct synchronizer on the pins of the low speed
                synchronizer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13030g2">Figure 162</hotlnk>). It is suggested that a shop towel be placed over the
                synchronizer to prevent injury to your hands.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13030g2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13030g2" filename="../figg13/G13030g2.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 162. Fully Seat Direct Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
